# Managed by dotfiles (config/roles/ssh). Edit in the repo, not here.
#
# Post-quantum SSH key exchange. OpenSSH's PQ protection lives in the key
# *exchange* (session confidentiality), which is what defends against
# "harvest-now, decrypt-later" attacks; host-key *authentication* has no
# standardized PQ signature algorithm yet, so nothing to do there.
#
# The leading '^' prepends these algorithms to OpenSSH's built-in default
# KexAlgorithms list, so classical algorithms remain available as fallbacks
# for older servers -- this prefers PQ rather than forcing it (PQ-only would
# break connections to pre-9.0 servers). Order = preference:
#   - mlkem768x25519-sha256                 ML-KEM (FIPS 203); OpenSSH 9.9+/10
#   - sntrup761x25519-sha512@openssh.com    NTRU Prime; default since OpenSSH 9.0
#
# NOTE: unknown algorithm names abort the client, so this fragment assumes a
# client that knows mlkem768x25519-sha256 (OpenSSH >= 9.9). The dev machines
# this repo provisions ship a current OpenSSH (Homebrew on macOS, rolling on
# Arch); see config/roles/ssh/README.md for the version audit.
Host *
  KexAlgorithms ^mlkem768x25519-sha256,sntrup761x25519-sha512@openssh.com
